    <note type="biography">
        <p>Author. Contributed fiction and social articles to numerous periodicals under the pen-name Silverpen. Her novels include <hi rend="italic">Struggles for fame</hi> (1845). An active member of the Whittington Club from 1846. Published a number of works about the Wedgwoods including a two-volume life of Josiah Wedgwood I (1865–6), and <hi rend="italic">The Wedgwood handbook</hi> (1875).</p></note>
